WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:08.458
♪ La-la-la-la, la-la-la-la ♪

00:08.541 --> 00:09.916
-[grunts]
-Mmm.

00:11.000 --> 00:12.541
[Centaurs laughing]

00:12.625 --> 00:15.458
Ooh-wow-wow!

00:15.541 --> 00:16.708
[laughing]

00:16.791 --> 00:18.750
I'm squashed. [laughs]

00:18.833 --> 00:22.416
Buh! Look at me.
Buh! I'm big B-B-B-Wammawink.

00:22.500 --> 00:24.291
Oh, B-B-B-Horse!

00:24.375 --> 00:28.916
Come see how weird your reflection looks
in the fun house b-b-b-mirror.

00:29.000 --> 00:31.666
I don't have to.
I look weird in every mirror.

00:31.750 --> 00:36.541
Oh, well, somebody put
one too many Bumblebeetaurs

00:36.625 --> 00:38.708
in the box spring mattress.

00:39.333 --> 00:42.250
Made of m-memory foam.

00:42.333 --> 00:43.291
[sighs]

00:44.541 --> 00:48.166
[Wammawink] ♪ In Centaurworld ♪

00:48.250 --> 00:50.916
-[neighing]
-[vocalizing]

00:51.000 --> 00:52.125
[squeaks]

00:53.166 --> 00:56.791
All right, everybody.
We made it to Merfolk Town!

00:56.875 --> 01:01.708
Home of the Whaletaur Shaman,
also known as the Last Shaman.

01:01.791 --> 01:04.583
Never understood why they called her that,
but here we are.

01:04.666 --> 01:06.833
Um, here's literally nobody here.

01:06.916 --> 01:10.458
I think you mean
there's figuratively nobody here.

01:11.208 --> 01:12.208
I mean, guys,

01:12.875 --> 01:13.875
are we…

01:14.500 --> 01:16.791
-[ominous music playing]
-…not here?

01:16.875 --> 01:21.750
It only appears there's no one here
because this is the land of Merdudes.

01:22.458 --> 01:26.625
They're probably underwater right now,
combing their glossy chest hair…

01:26.708 --> 01:28.333
[groovy music playing]

01:28.416 --> 01:30.166
…flexing their rippling gills…

01:30.250 --> 01:31.375
[wolf whistles]

01:32.458 --> 01:36.291
…laying their merman eggs,
but in a hot way.

01:36.375 --> 01:38.166
[male voice] I'm suffocatin' down here!

01:38.250 --> 01:41.125
Okay, this is the last thing
I need right now.

01:41.208 --> 01:44.375
Oh… [clears throat]
Well, if you'd like to learn more,

01:44.458 --> 01:47.833
you can refer to
this educational magazine I-- they found.

01:48.666 --> 01:51.083
Wammawink, you made that magazine.

01:51.166 --> 01:52.083
I helped you!

01:52.166 --> 01:54.875
You said if I didn't help you,
I wouldn't get Gigglecakes.

01:54.958 --> 01:58.166
-[laughing] Okay, Glendale.
-That's not even the only issue!

01:58.250 --> 01:59.916
-There's many!
-Good angle.

02:00.000 --> 02:03.666
Some of 'em were wearing swimsuits.
Some of 'em were wearing makeup.

02:03.750 --> 02:05.958
You made me draw so many merman eggs.

02:06.041 --> 02:08.250
[chuckling] Oh, well, I mean, uh…

02:08.333 --> 02:11.916
There was the September issue.
There was the fireman issue.

02:12.000 --> 02:15.250
There was the holiday issue.
There was the pirate issue.

02:15.333 --> 02:18.208
There was the sports issue.
There were so many issues!

02:18.791 --> 02:21.458
You made me write all those quizzes
and do horoscopes.

02:21.541 --> 02:24.041
I don't like horoscopes!
I don't believe in that stuff.

02:24.125 --> 02:26.208
There's this pillow you made me sew.

02:26.291 --> 02:28.583
You made me draw a man on it,
a merman on it.

02:28.666 --> 02:30.583
Okay, Glendale. Okay!

02:30.666 --> 02:35.083
The… The point is,
there are supposed to be Merdudes here.

02:35.166 --> 02:37.541
[male voice] Merdudes? You mean, like me?

02:39.500 --> 02:40.500
Uh…

02:41.000 --> 02:42.125
Oh…

02:42.208 --> 02:44.125
Wait. I… Oh.

02:52.333 --> 02:53.958
-Hello there.
-[screams]

02:54.041 --> 02:55.750
I mean, um… [clearing throat]

02:55.833 --> 03:00.166
[chuckles nervously] So, you…
you're a… a Merdude?

03:00.250 --> 03:02.375
Yep, in the flesh.

03:02.458 --> 03:03.583
Are you sure?

03:03.666 --> 03:06.875
Merdudes usually have glossy chest hair,

03:06.958 --> 03:08.541
rippling gills…

03:09.458 --> 03:11.958
-They lay their eggs like this.
-[shudders]

03:12.041 --> 03:16.041
No. The eggs actually come from here.

03:16.125 --> 03:17.125
[sighs]

03:17.625 --> 03:21.875
I'm sorry I touched your hand.
You're a great artist, by the way.

03:21.958 --> 03:23.375
Oh, thanks.

03:24.000 --> 03:26.166
Where are the other Merdudes?

03:26.250 --> 03:29.125
[chuckling] Well,
when it comes to Merdudes,

03:29.208 --> 03:32.083
Sunfish's Merguy's kind of
the only game in town.

03:32.625 --> 03:34.916
Except for those guys.

03:35.000 --> 03:36.208
[squeaks]

03:36.291 --> 03:41.291
[chuckles] I'm sure you all didn't come
all this way down to Merfolk Town

03:42.083 --> 03:45.500
♪ Just to sit and watch the sun go down ♪

03:45.583 --> 03:48.250
-Now, did you?
-No. We're here to see the Shaman--

03:48.333 --> 03:50.250
♪ I'll just stop you there ♪

03:50.333 --> 03:52.666
♪ You see, I've heard this all before ♪

03:52.750 --> 03:56.375
♪ Everybody wants the same thing
When they come down to the shore ♪

03:56.458 --> 03:58.833
♪ No, I'm sorry
There's no time, you see ♪

03:58.916 --> 04:02.833
♪ I've been here in this world too long
Look, I've become a different thing ♪

04:02.916 --> 04:05.000
♪ I can't stop to sing another song ♪

04:05.750 --> 04:06.958
Sorry. [chuckles]

04:07.041 --> 04:11.166
You'll have to excuse my friend.
She gets a little emotional sometimes.

04:11.250 --> 04:13.666
-Did you say your name was…
-Sunfish Merguy.

04:13.750 --> 04:16.666
-Sunfish Merguy. Oh.
-Well, it's not my real name.

04:16.750 --> 04:17.750
My real name is…

04:17.833 --> 04:19.083
[clicking]

04:20.500 --> 04:25.125
But that's a little hard to pronounce,
so I just go by Sunfish Merguy.

04:25.208 --> 04:28.208
Oh, well, my name's Wimmawink.
Pleased to meet you--

04:28.291 --> 04:29.416
All right! Clear out!

04:29.500 --> 04:30.750
-Durpleton!
-What?

04:30.833 --> 04:32.666
Nobody cares about your name, Wammawink.

04:32.750 --> 04:35.416
Did you hear this guy?
He said he's got games!

04:35.500 --> 04:38.666
Oh yeah. That's right.
I got a lot of games.

04:38.750 --> 04:39.875
Oh yeah? Like what?

04:40.375 --> 04:43.333
♪ Well, I got whack-a-mole, ring toss
Throw a ball, dunk a clown ♪

04:43.416 --> 04:45.125
♪ You can play any game
Don't sit around ♪

04:45.208 --> 04:47.166
♪ Milk bottle, duck pond
Throw darts at balloons ♪

04:47.250 --> 04:49.125
♪ Get your face drawn
Stack prizes to the moon ♪

04:49.208 --> 04:50.833
♪ If you've come to see the Shaman ♪

04:50.916 --> 04:53.500
-♪ You might be waiting quite some time ♪
-♪ Could be a while ♪

04:53.583 --> 04:56.833
♪ Lucky you, at Sunfish Merguy's
You'll never wait in any lines ♪

04:56.916 --> 04:58.250
♪ 'Cause there's no one here ♪

04:58.333 --> 05:00.166
♪ Rope ladder, skeet shoot
Throw a coin into a boot ♪

05:00.250 --> 05:02.208
♪ Pet a dolphin, have a hot dog
Shoot a basket, win loot ♪

05:02.291 --> 05:04.125
♪ Another hot dog, soda fountain
Pirate patch, gold doubloons ♪

05:04.208 --> 05:06.000
♪ Eat lots of cotton candy
Save some room! ♪

05:06.083 --> 05:10.000
♪ If you've come to see the Shaman
You might be waiting quite some time ♪

05:10.083 --> 05:13.791
♪ Lucky you, at Sunfish Merguy's
You'll never wait in any lines ♪

05:13.875 --> 05:15.416
♪ 'Cause there's no one here! ♪

05:15.500 --> 05:19.541
♪ There's so many games for you to play
While waiting at the bay ♪

05:19.625 --> 05:22.291
♪ So do what you want to do ♪

05:22.375 --> 05:24.250
I wanna see the Shaman.

05:24.333 --> 05:26.291
♪ Anything but that ♪

05:26.375 --> 05:29.458
♪ I mean
There's technically a possibility ♪

05:29.541 --> 05:34.083
♪ Your herd will get to see
The Shaman visit us today right here ♪

05:34.166 --> 05:35.416
♪ Down on the isle ♪

05:36.041 --> 05:41.958
♪ My guess?
It's gonna be a while ♪

05:44.583 --> 05:48.750
[groans] When does the Shaman get here?
Later this afternoon? After sundown?

05:48.833 --> 05:49.916
[winces]

05:50.000 --> 05:52.416
Yeah, see, it could be this afternoon.

05:52.500 --> 05:56.416
But it's much more likely
that you won't see her today.

05:56.500 --> 05:59.125
Or this week.
You guys want some free tokens?

05:59.625 --> 06:01.666
-[dramatic music plays]
-[grunting]

06:02.291 --> 06:05.041
You guys, I don't trust this guy,
not one bit.

06:05.125 --> 06:07.333
-I think he wants something.
-I think…

06:08.791 --> 06:10.333
he just wants to hang out.

06:10.416 --> 06:13.916
-What did you think, Horse?
-I think the Shaman's not here.

06:14.000 --> 06:17.083
I think I look like
two beach balls had a weird kid.

06:18.458 --> 06:21.416
I think I'm gonna take a walk
before I lose it completely.

06:21.500 --> 06:23.875
Ooh! [giggles] Oh my.

06:23.958 --> 06:25.750
Oh. Mmm.

06:25.833 --> 06:27.250
Where are you going?

06:27.333 --> 06:29.416
Not home any time soon.

06:29.500 --> 06:32.375
Okay. I'll hold our place in line.

06:32.916 --> 06:35.666
You were saying something
I suddenly find fascinating?

06:35.750 --> 06:38.125
I know what we can do to cheer Horse up.

06:38.875 --> 06:41.583
-Play games!
-That's gonna cheer you up. No.

06:41.666 --> 06:42.750
Exactly.

06:42.833 --> 06:44.833
She does seem pretty down.

06:44.916 --> 06:48.000
Maybe we could steal her--
Win her a prize.

06:48.083 --> 06:51.000
That might make me-- Horse feel better.

06:51.083 --> 06:52.458
Games!

06:54.875 --> 06:56.375
[chittering]

06:58.458 --> 07:00.000
[wind whooshing]

07:04.916 --> 07:08.208
You look so wrong.

07:08.291 --> 07:10.375
Yeah? Well, so do you!

07:11.458 --> 07:14.791
Uh, I know.
I was talking to my reflection.

07:14.875 --> 07:16.583
Oh, now, hey, come on.

07:16.666 --> 07:18.958
Don't be so hard on yourself.
You look fine.

07:19.041 --> 07:23.375
Hey, Barnus? I can't see what
this thing looks like. Describe it to me.

07:23.458 --> 07:26.416
It's like if two beach balls
had a weird kid.

07:27.166 --> 07:30.750
-I don't know what I'm lookin' at here.
-Why don't ya ask it?

07:30.833 --> 07:33.000
Oh yeah. Hey, what are you?

07:33.083 --> 07:34.208
I heard him.

07:34.916 --> 07:38.083
[sighs] I don't know what I am anymore.

07:39.500 --> 07:41.750
I think we hurt its feelings, Sean.

07:43.708 --> 07:45.708
[somber music playing]

07:58.791 --> 08:00.041
[rumbling]

08:01.250 --> 08:02.375
[gasps]

08:03.041 --> 08:05.125
[whalesong]

08:08.875 --> 08:11.333
[gasps] Are you the Shaman?

08:12.416 --> 08:13.500
[Whaletaur] I am.

08:13.583 --> 08:16.625
Sunfish Merguy said
it would be a while before you came back.

08:16.708 --> 08:20.333
Did he now? Well, clearly that's not true,
because I'm here.

08:22.750 --> 08:24.666
I was summoned by your teardrop.

08:29.875 --> 08:33.000
♪ Hello, hello
It's nice to meet you ♪

08:33.583 --> 08:35.916
♪ I'm here to greet you ♪

08:36.000 --> 08:39.541
♪ And not to--
Oh, why don't we talk about the bay? ♪

08:39.625 --> 08:43.291
♪ My bay
Its waves so green and see-through ♪

08:43.375 --> 08:45.541
♪ Just down beneath you ♪

08:46.166 --> 08:48.291
♪ Where the merfolk swim and play ♪

08:48.375 --> 08:52.666
♪ And if you're feeling blue
I've got the place for you ♪

08:52.750 --> 08:57.541
♪ In me
I promise I'll consume all of your pain ♪

08:57.625 --> 09:00.708
♪ Oh, I know sadness when I see it ♪

09:00.791 --> 09:04.083
♪ And I'm here
So you don't feel that way again ♪

09:04.166 --> 09:10.375
♪ Hello, hello
I see you're eyeing my constant crying ♪

09:10.458 --> 09:13.333
♪ It's not easy doing what I do ♪

09:13.416 --> 09:17.083
♪ But I must go on
Seeking all those sighing ♪

09:17.166 --> 09:20.000
♪ The woeful asking why-ing ♪

09:20.083 --> 09:22.625
♪ I'll help them-- [laughs]
Let's move on ♪

09:22.708 --> 09:27.333
♪ When you are feeling sad
When life's become too bad ♪

09:27.416 --> 09:32.166
♪ I can absorb your grief
And numb it all away ♪

09:32.250 --> 09:34.833
♪ You can fade in blissful peace ♪

09:34.916 --> 09:38.833
♪ And have one restful, gentle
Happy final day ♪

09:39.416 --> 09:43.916
♪ I want to help the suffering beings ♪

09:44.000 --> 09:48.541
♪ I keep seeing everywhere ♪

09:49.125 --> 09:55.958
♪ This is the kindness I can share ♪

09:59.500 --> 10:01.000
♪ So ♪

10:02.250 --> 10:07.291
♪ Tell me what ails you, child ♪

10:11.375 --> 10:13.416
[sighs] Where do I begin?

10:14.875 --> 10:17.708
I've never sat for a caricature before.

10:17.791 --> 10:20.041
[laughing] Oh, I don't do caricatures.

10:20.541 --> 10:22.250
This is for journalism.

10:22.333 --> 10:23.333
Trust me.

10:23.833 --> 10:26.375
It will be very flattering.

10:27.000 --> 10:28.541
I'm counting on it.

10:28.625 --> 10:30.125
[giggling]

10:30.791 --> 10:33.458
So, you just need my piece of the key?

10:35.333 --> 10:36.541
[gags]

10:36.625 --> 10:40.791
Usually, when someone comes to me,
they want to escape this world.

10:40.875 --> 10:44.416
Which, technically, you do, too,
but to another world.

10:45.166 --> 10:46.833
Not the one inside my belly.

10:48.125 --> 10:49.791
But that's the real problem.

10:49.875 --> 10:51.916
Even if I make it back to my world,
to Rider,

10:52.000 --> 10:54.416
I won't be the Horse she remembers.

10:54.500 --> 10:56.333
Is she even gonna recognize me?

10:57.041 --> 10:58.791
Will she still need me?

10:58.875 --> 11:00.458
Why wouldn't she?

11:00.541 --> 11:02.208
I don't even recognize me.

11:02.291 --> 11:05.458
I sing, I dance, my tail tells bad jokes.

11:05.541 --> 11:08.541
-[Tail] Hey-o!
-I guess I'm two beach balls now.

11:08.625 --> 11:10.416
Who doesn't like beach balls?

11:10.500 --> 11:11.958
[Tail laughing]

11:12.041 --> 11:15.708
The worst part, and I haven't even
admitted this to Wammawink,

11:15.791 --> 11:17.208
[somber music playing]

11:17.291 --> 11:19.708
I don't know if I'd even recognize Rider.

11:21.166 --> 11:24.208
Ever since these changes started,

11:24.958 --> 11:27.458
her face started to fade from my memory.

11:27.958 --> 11:33.083
I close my eyes, and my strongest memory
is the pain of losing her.

11:34.375 --> 11:36.208
[Centaurs] Wammawink!

11:36.291 --> 11:38.291
Check it out! See? Wammawink!

11:38.375 --> 11:40.583
-Wammawink!
-Wammawink!

11:42.083 --> 11:43.666
Wammawink! Seriously!

11:43.750 --> 11:47.375
Oh, I get it.
This guy doesn't wanna hang out at all.

11:47.458 --> 11:48.666
He wants Wammawink.

11:48.750 --> 11:50.666
What are you doing?

11:50.750 --> 11:53.166
[yelling] Why are you doing?

11:53.250 --> 11:54.750
[whimpering]

11:54.833 --> 11:57.875
Well, he's not my dad.
Hey, I am not calling you Dad.

11:57.958 --> 11:59.458
Settle down. [chuckles nervously]

11:59.541 --> 12:01.291
Show me what you got for Horse.

12:02.125 --> 12:03.375
[grunts]

12:03.458 --> 12:06.375
A Whaletaur floaty? Where'd you get this?

12:06.458 --> 12:08.625
We won it.

12:09.416 --> 12:10.375
[glass shatters]

12:10.458 --> 12:12.916
Very ethically. Right, guys?

12:13.000 --> 12:14.416
[Centaurs] Uh…

12:14.500 --> 12:17.416
This is the perfect thing
to cheer up our Horse.

12:17.500 --> 12:19.541
I don't think you'll need to cheer her up.

12:19.625 --> 12:21.041
[whalesong]

12:22.041 --> 12:26.750
Oh, you said it would be a while
before the Whaletaur Shaman showed up.

12:26.833 --> 12:28.458
Uh… Mmm.

12:29.083 --> 12:30.958
It looks like she's gonna sing!

12:31.666 --> 12:34.375
Oh, things are really looking up
for her, guys.

12:36.041 --> 12:40.916
♪ Help me
I think I'm far too gone ♪

12:41.833 --> 12:48.125
♪ And my reflection has become
An unfamiliar someone ♪

12:48.791 --> 12:54.166
♪ So close
But I think I'm stuck in place ♪

12:54.958 --> 13:01.458
♪ I don't deserve you
Now that I forgot your face ♪

13:05.875 --> 13:07.708
♪ Who is she? ♪

13:08.291 --> 13:12.416
♪ She's the ghost of the girl
I used to know ♪

13:12.500 --> 13:14.500
♪ Who is she? ♪

13:15.333 --> 13:18.750
♪ She's the echo I'm chasing ♪

13:19.541 --> 13:21.750
♪ Who is she? ♪

13:22.416 --> 13:26.458
♪ Oh, I swore that I'd never let her go ♪

13:26.541 --> 13:32.500
♪ And now the one I held so dear
My mind's erasing ♪

13:33.583 --> 13:37.000
♪ It takes a little boldness ♪

13:37.958 --> 13:41.166
♪ And a little bit of magic ♪

13:42.541 --> 13:47.041
♪ I went on my own
But now I'm alone ♪

13:47.125 --> 13:51.000
♪ I'm lost and I am panicked ♪

13:54.166 --> 13:59.458
♪ I think I should go into the unknown ♪

14:02.791 --> 14:04.875
♪ So say bye ♪

14:04.958 --> 14:11.625
♪ To the old ♪

14:13.875 --> 14:16.333
[dramatic music playing]

14:34.458 --> 14:37.041
Ah! Look at that sunset.

14:37.625 --> 14:39.375
Love this time of day.

14:39.458 --> 14:42.416
Our friend just jumped into a Whaletaur,
you psychopath!

14:42.500 --> 14:43.541
[crying]

14:43.625 --> 14:48.166
Whoa, ladies. Didn't you know
she was gonna swallow your friend?

14:48.250 --> 14:50.750
-[all] No!
-Why would we have guessed that?

14:50.833 --> 14:53.166
But you were holding her place in line.

14:53.750 --> 14:55.875
[Zulius] "Ride the Whaletaur Shaman."

14:55.958 --> 14:59.666
"The journey of zero miles
begins with a single step"?

14:59.750 --> 15:02.000
"You must be this despondent to ride"?

15:02.083 --> 15:08.000
You guys! The Whaletaur floaty
is full of tiny Centaurs!

15:08.583 --> 15:11.000
-[whimpering]
-Why would somebody choose that?

15:11.083 --> 15:15.541
I try to give people fun things to do.
I got all these cool games and rides.

15:15.625 --> 15:19.541
But everyone always chooses the whale.
And they never come out again.

15:20.041 --> 15:22.041
[chuckling] Oh, she's coming out.

15:25.916 --> 15:30.916
[Whaletaur] Everyone, let's give our
new friend Horse a big Whaletaur welcome.

15:31.916 --> 15:32.916
Everyone?

15:33.458 --> 15:35.333
There's nobody here.

15:36.250 --> 15:37.416
Where am I?

15:38.666 --> 15:39.916
[gasps]

15:41.625 --> 15:44.000
Oh. It's just you, Gebbrey.

15:44.625 --> 15:46.416
What are you doing here?

15:46.500 --> 15:50.458
I think I was looking for something.

15:51.416 --> 15:53.208
I don't remember.

15:53.708 --> 15:57.041
-[jazz music playing]
-Oh man. Isn't music the best?

15:57.125 --> 15:58.750
[music continues]

16:02.000 --> 16:03.791
Get me as close as you can.

16:03.875 --> 16:05.250
[gasps]

16:05.333 --> 16:06.916
I'll block her path!

16:07.000 --> 16:08.833
[adventurous music playing]

16:11.000 --> 16:12.666
Durpleton, you can't swim.

16:13.833 --> 16:15.166
[Durpleton screaming]

16:17.250 --> 16:19.250
[screaming]

16:20.083 --> 16:21.250
[clears throat]

16:21.333 --> 16:23.916
I'm not swimming. I'm standing!

16:24.000 --> 16:25.333
On what?

16:25.416 --> 16:26.875
On the…

16:27.458 --> 16:30.083
uh, down there.

16:31.958 --> 16:35.125
Barnus, describe it to me.

16:35.208 --> 16:37.541
Oh boy. Oh, this one's gonna be hard.

16:38.708 --> 16:39.916
[blowhole whooshing]

16:40.958 --> 16:43.250
Zulius, Shapely Mane me some rope.

16:43.333 --> 16:45.291
What for?

16:45.375 --> 16:47.458
-I'll go down the blowhole--
-[all] Holes!

16:47.541 --> 16:50.708
…get Horse, tug on the rope,
and then you'll know to pull us out.

16:50.791 --> 16:53.666
[scoffs] Fine, but don't get it wet.

16:56.083 --> 16:57.333
[grunting]

16:57.416 --> 16:58.541
Huh!

17:01.000 --> 17:02.541
[blowhole whooshing]

17:02.625 --> 17:04.625
[dramatic music playing]

17:06.791 --> 17:08.000
[groans]

17:08.083 --> 17:12.125
[all chanting] Conga, conga,
conga, conga, conga.

17:12.208 --> 17:13.833
Conga, conga, conga.

17:13.916 --> 17:15.208
-[thuds]
-[Wammawink grunts]

17:15.291 --> 17:16.541
-Horse!
-Ah.

17:16.625 --> 17:19.666
-Come on. We've got to get out of here.
-You're right.

17:19.750 --> 17:22.708
The shuffleboard tournament starts soon.

17:22.791 --> 17:25.583
Horse, it's me. It's Wammawink.

17:25.666 --> 17:28.166
[Whaletaur] Everyone, Wammawink's here.

17:28.250 --> 17:31.916
Would've been nice if she came in
like everybody else, but she's here now,

17:32.000 --> 17:33.708
so let's give our new friend

17:33.791 --> 17:36.125
a Whaletaur welcome.

17:36.208 --> 17:39.833
You can give me a Whaletaur goodbye,
because we're leaving!

17:39.916 --> 17:42.958
[slurring] Yeah. We're goin' to
the shuffleboard tournament.

17:43.916 --> 17:46.000
What have you done to her?

17:46.083 --> 17:48.166
[Whaletaur] I absorbed her pain.

17:48.750 --> 17:53.375
All these folks chose me as
the final resting place for their sorrow.

17:53.458 --> 17:57.666
And I feel their pain more than anyone.

17:57.750 --> 18:03.166
Conga, conga, conga, conga, conga, conga.

18:03.250 --> 18:06.791
Conga, conga, conga. [screams]

18:06.875 --> 18:09.583
Hey, everybody! Look up here.
Yeah, look at me.

18:10.666 --> 18:13.291
Pain stinks. I get it.

18:13.375 --> 18:14.416
I have pain, too.

18:15.500 --> 18:19.208
[sighs] I know it hurts to remember,
but you have to.

18:19.291 --> 18:23.083
You have to remember me.
You have to remember the herd.

18:23.666 --> 18:25.666
You have to remember Rider.

18:26.291 --> 18:27.291
[snorts]

18:27.375 --> 18:28.583
Rider?

18:29.333 --> 18:33.416
You have to keep going.
You are not alone in this.

18:36.083 --> 18:37.416
[drum sticks tapping]

18:37.541 --> 18:42.791
♪ We are all just fragile things
Soft and small ♪

18:42.875 --> 18:49.791
♪ And oh, I know
That life is full of suffering and pain ♪

18:49.875 --> 18:50.875
♪ But ♪

18:52.541 --> 18:56.541
♪ All the broken can find hope in ♪

18:56.625 --> 18:59.875
♪ The most unexpected places ♪

18:59.958 --> 19:03.625
♪ Love still finds us
Family finds us ♪

19:03.708 --> 19:08.625
♪ Even if we can't make out their faces ♪

19:10.208 --> 19:13.916
♪ Even an orphaned baby girl ♪

19:14.000 --> 19:17.666
♪ Can find a new herd of her own ♪

19:17.750 --> 19:22.125
♪ And a warrior from a different world ♪

19:22.208 --> 19:29.166
♪ Can find love so far from home ♪

19:32.708 --> 19:39.583
[Whaletaur] ♪ Hello, hello
It's nice to meet you ♪

19:49.750 --> 19:52.000
I thought that everyone who came to me

19:52.083 --> 19:54.916
was here
because they had no other options.

19:55.000 --> 19:58.875
If I'd known there was another way
for their spirits to be lifted…

19:58.958 --> 20:00.625
It's not too late.

20:03.500 --> 20:04.500
Ow!

20:04.583 --> 20:06.083
[water gushing]

20:07.541 --> 20:08.916
[all screaming]

20:10.583 --> 20:11.791
[rumbling]

20:12.916 --> 20:14.916
[screaming]

20:16.666 --> 20:17.916
-[yelling]
-What was that?

20:18.000 --> 20:19.666
[screaming, grunting]

20:22.666 --> 20:23.666
[Zulius screams]

20:23.750 --> 20:25.708
[Whaletaur] Is everyone coming? I gotta--

20:25.791 --> 20:27.083
-[screaming]
-So cold!

20:27.166 --> 20:28.708
[heaves, mumbles]

20:28.791 --> 20:29.791
[grunts]

20:29.875 --> 20:31.375
[all screaming]

20:32.458 --> 20:33.416
Ugh!

20:35.500 --> 20:36.416
[gags]

20:38.166 --> 20:41.333
-[Whaletaur] I thought I was helping.
-[Wammawink grunts]

20:41.416 --> 20:47.166
But I was depriving them of life,
complete with its beauty and rough edges.

20:47.250 --> 20:48.250
[Ched yelps]

20:48.333 --> 20:50.000
-[screaming]
-[snorts]

20:50.083 --> 20:51.375
[squeaks, groans]

20:52.500 --> 20:53.625
[Whaletaur] Take it.

20:56.791 --> 20:58.000
Finish your mission.

20:58.791 --> 21:01.833
I don't know what you'll find
on the other side of the rift.

21:02.333 --> 21:05.916
But I do know that there are those
on this side who'll be there for you

21:06.000 --> 21:07.833
-no matter what.
-[snorts]

21:07.916 --> 21:11.250
[sighs] Thank you. And thanks, Wammawink.

21:11.875 --> 21:17.416
Horse, we got you a going away gift
of this important scarf.

21:17.500 --> 21:18.500
Oh, uh…

21:19.833 --> 21:20.833
I love it.

21:21.375 --> 21:23.333
-Here. I drew this.
-[screams]

21:23.416 --> 21:25.416
Thank you?

21:26.083 --> 21:27.458
Oops. [chuckles]

21:27.541 --> 21:29.916
That one's mine. For journalism.

21:30.000 --> 21:31.833
Uh, this one is for you.

21:32.333 --> 21:33.333
[sighs]

21:34.041 --> 21:35.166
It's perfect.

21:35.250 --> 21:39.291
Mind if I grab that cool drawing
you did of me? Jeffica's gonna love it.

21:39.375 --> 21:41.791
-[shrill scream]
-Who is… [laughs]

21:41.875 --> 21:42.916
Jeffica?

21:43.541 --> 21:44.791
My girlfriend.

21:45.500 --> 21:47.875
[laughing] Oh, your girlfriend. Oh, yeah.

21:47.958 --> 21:50.375
Yeah, sure. Yeah, for Jeffica.

21:54.500 --> 21:58.416
Sweet. Thanks!
Taking this straight to the framer.

21:58.500 --> 21:59.708
See you, buddy.

22:00.625 --> 22:02.291
-[snorts]
-[sighs]

22:02.833 --> 22:07.166
That's what I get for liking someone
for their… [inhales] personality.

22:07.250 --> 22:08.250
Hmm.

22:08.333 --> 22:11.416
[sighs] Wish I hadn't spent
one of my last days with you guys

22:11.500 --> 22:13.833
completely paralyzed by my own sadness.

22:13.916 --> 22:17.625
Are you kidding?
Horse, you're allowed to be sad.

22:17.708 --> 22:18.708
It's coo.

22:19.166 --> 22:21.000
-Thanks, Wammawink.
-[chuckling]

22:21.083 --> 22:24.750
Horse can't escape
the cuddle cuddle bye-bye zone! Mmm.

22:24.833 --> 22:27.750
We're not saying goodbye
until we make it to the rift.

22:27.833 --> 22:29.375
Come on, guys. Let's go.

22:29.458 --> 22:31.541
But we don't want to.

22:32.291 --> 22:34.166
Uh, Durpleton?

22:34.250 --> 22:35.916
Where's the rest of you?

22:36.000 --> 22:37.041
[chuckles]

22:37.541 --> 22:39.333
It's, uh…

22:39.416 --> 22:41.166
Oh, I… I got it! I got it!

22:41.250 --> 22:42.500
It's kinda like a…

22:42.583 --> 22:44.000
Yeah? Yeah?

22:44.583 --> 22:46.125
Never mind! It's gone now!

22:47.458 --> 22:49.458
[closing theme music playing]

23:18.958 --> 23:20.916
[Horse galloping]

23:21.000 --> 23:23.208
[neighing]

23:23.916 --> 23:25.916
[whimsical music playing]
